20 Libertarian Party Presidential Preference |website=The Jack News|date=July 17, 2017 |access-date=October 16, 2017}}</ref>\n| July 9\u201315, 2017\n| \u2014\n| 6%\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| 6%\n| 10.2%\n| \u2014\n| 10.2%\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| -\n| \u2014\n| -\n| -\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''16%'''\n| -\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''43%'''\n| Undecided 8%\n|-\n|A Libertarian Future<ref>{{cite web |url=https://alibertarianfuture.com/2020/libertarian-presidential-candidates/poll-support-for-2020-libertarian-presidential-nomination/ |access-date=October 14, 2017|website=A Libertarian Future|title=POLL: Who Do You Support For The 2020 Libertarian Presidential Nomination?}}</ref>\n| March 2017\n| 8%\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| 4%\n| \u2014\n| 2%\n| 3%\n| \u2014\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''26%'''\n| 1%\n| 18%\n| -\n| 1%\n| \u2014\n| -\n| -\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''25%'''\n| 3%\n| 8%\n| None of the Above 1%\n|-\n|A Libertarian Future<ref>{{cite web |url=https://alibertarianfuture.com/2020/poll-who-would-you-support-for-the-libertarian-presidential-nom-in-2020/ |access-date=October 14, 2017|website=A Libertarian Future|title=POLL: Who Would You Support For The Libertarian Presidential Nom In 2020?}}</ref>\n| November 2016\n| 5%\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| 10%\n| \u2014\n| 1%\n| 3%\n| \u2014\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''33%'''\n| 1%\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''27%'''\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| 6%\n| 4%\n| 9%\n| -\n| -\n| None of the Above 1%\n|}\n\n== Campaign finance ==\nThis is an overview of the money used by each campaign as it is reported to the [[Federal Election Commission]] (FEC) and released on October 15, 2019. Totals raised include loans from the candidate and transfers from other campaign committees. Some of the Libertarian candidates have not filed with the FEC, and financial data for those candidates are therefore not available.\n\n{{legend|silver|Withdrawn candid