ff |url=https://www.facebook.com/kim.ruff2020/posts/184401506118530 |website=www.facebook.com |access-date=23 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n;State legislators\n* [[Caleb Q. Dyer]], former [[New Hampshire House of Representatives|New Hampshire State Representative]] from Hillsborough District 37 (2017\u20132019)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/repcqdyer/posts/1419053788263774?__tn__=-R |title=Caleb Q. Dyer |via=www.facebook.com}}</ref>\n* [[Brandon Phinney]], former [[New Hampshire House of Representatives|New Hampshire State Representative]] from Strafford District 24 (2017\u20132019)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/phinney/posts/898408247001|title=Brandon Phinney |via=www.facebook.com}}</ref> ''(Previously endorsed Ruff)''\n;Municipal officials\n* Spencer Dias, member of the [[Goffstown, New Hampshire]] budget committee and Vice Chair of Southern New Hampshire Libertarian Party<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/vermin.supreme.1/posts/3006970402669448 |title=Vermin Supreme |website=www.facebook.com}}</ref>\n* Richard Manzo, member of the Goffstown, New Hampshire budget committee, trustee of the [[Goffstown Public Library]], and Vice Chair of the [[Libertarian Party of New Hampshire]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/RichardManzoNH/status/1203870568044548096 |title=Richard Manzo \u2013 Twitter}}</ref>\n;Party officials\n* Brent DeRidder, Vice Chair of the [[Libertarian Party of North Carolina]]\n* Matt Hicks, 2nd Vice Chair of the [[Libertarian Party of South Carolina]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/vermin.supreme.1/posts/3032268450139643 |title=Vermin Supreme |website=www.facebook.com}}</ref>\n* Peyton Kunselman, Secretary of the [[Cattaraugus County, New York|Cattaraugus County, NY]] Libertarian Party<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/peyton.kunselman.5/posts/601453137341699:0 |title=Peyton Kunselman |website=www.facebook.com}}</ref>\n* Eric Mulder, Vice Chair of the [[Libertarian Party of 